<h1>Calculating Tuition</h1>
<p>Please note that tuition is based on how many BYU-Idaho course credits a student is taking per semester. A course credit is a measurement universities use to quantify the load of work for a specific course and enables universities to quantify a requirement to graduate. Each course is associated with a different credit amount.</p>
<p><strong>Age 18-30 Group </strong><em>(U.S./Canada)</em><strong></strong><br /> <em>Fall &amp; Winter Semesters: </em><br /> $65 per credit x 3 BYU-Idaho credits = $195 per semester <br /> $0 per credit x 2 institute credits = $0 per semester<br /><br /> <em>Spring Semester*: </em><br /> $65 per credit x 5 BYU-Idaho credits = $325 per semester</p>
<p><em>*Students will take a BYU-Idaho online religion course which is 2 credits in addition to their regular 3-credit course.</em><br /><br /> <strong>Age 31+ Group </strong><em>(U.S./Canada)</em><strong></strong><br /> <em>Fall, Winter, &amp; Spring Semesters: </em><br /> $65 per credit x 5 BYU-Idaho credits = $325 per semester</p>
<p><strong>ESL Group </strong><em>(U.S./Canada)</em><strong></strong><br /> <em>Fall, Winter, &amp; Spring Semesters: </em><br /> $45 per credit x 5 BYU-Idaho credits = $225 per semester</p>
<p><strong>International</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Groups</strong> <br /> <em>Fall, Winter, &amp; Spring Semesters: </em><br /> Mexico: $35 per credit x 5 BYU-Idaho&nbsp;credits = $175&nbsp;per semester<br /> Peru: $30 per credit x 5 BYU-Idaho&nbsp;credits = $150&nbsp;per semester<br />Ghana: $20 per credit x 5 BYU-Idaho credits = $100 per semester</p>
<h1 id="HowToMakeAPayment">How to Make a Payment</h1>
<p><strong>Domestic Students</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Online Payment Method Procedure.pdf">Online</a> with credit card or debit card. (Visa is now <span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span>accepted.)</li>
<li><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Online Payment Method Procedure.pdf">Online</a> &nbsp;with electronic check.</li>
<li><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Online Payment Method Procedure.pdf">Online</a> &nbsp;with wire transfer (in US Dollars).</li>
<li>Mail a check to BYU-Idaho Bursar's Office, 525 S Center Street, Rexburg, ID 83460-1625.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>International Students</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Online Payment Method Procedure.pdf">Online</a> &nbsp;with credit card or debit card. (Visa is accepted.)</li>
<li><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Online Payment Method Procedure.pdf">Online</a> &nbsp;with wire transfer. This is facilitated through Western Union. Students must take into account processing fees, exchange rate, and processing time. Students must also have a bank account - cash transactions are not an option. Students must print a PDF form and take it with them to their bank. At the top of the form there is important routing information that the bank will use to route money to BYU-Idaho.</li>
</ul>
<h1>Tuition Information<strong> </strong></h1>
<ul>
<li>Payment for tuition is always <strong>due the first day of class</strong>.</li>
<li>If you register late, tuition is due upon registration.</li>
<li>A late charge of 5%&nbsp;of the unpaid balance will be assessed for any late payments seven days following the the first day of the semester. A service charge of 1% per month will be charged each month for any unpaid balance.</li>
<li>The only way to get a full refund is if you withdraw from your course within the first seven days of the semester. If you completely withdraw after the first seven days you will receive a prorated refund.</li>
<li>If you withdraw after the first seven days of the semester and have not yet paid your tuition you will still owe a prorated amount.</li>
</ul>
<h1>Can I Receive Financial Assistance?</h1>
<p>U.S. students who have a high school diploma or GED may apply for Federal Financial Aid after you complete Academic Start and apply to BYU-Idaho as a degree-seeking student. For more information about eligibility contact the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/FinancialAid/">financial aid office</a>.</p>
<p>International students may be eligible for a <a href="http://pef.lds.org/pef/aboutus?locale=eng">Perpetual Education Fund</a> (PEF) loan or other assistance. Contact your <a href="x46402.xml">local Pathway Missionaries</a> for more information. &nbsp;</p>
